FT  20 JAN 93 / Parliament and Politics: Tenants to fund housing benefit
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
ALMOST Pounds 800m of the housing benefit available to council tenants in
England will be funded by other tenants next year, according to figures
highlighted by Mr Nick Raynsford, Labour MP for Greenwich.
Mr Raynsford said the amount of housing benefit which had to be found from
council tenants had risen from Pounds 200m in 1990-91 to Pounds 792m in
1993-94. This represented an average of Pounds 3.85 per week for every
council tenant, and meant that in most local authorities' areas tenants
would have to make some contribution, he added.
