FT  20 JAN 93 / Ex-Soviet debt accord
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRYSTIA FREELAND and LEYLA BOULTON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KIEV, MOSCOW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
DETAILS of an agreement dividing the foreign debts and assets of the former
Soviet Union between Ukraine and Russia were yesterday released in Kiev,
write Chrystia Freeland from Kiev and Leyla Boulton from Moscow.
According to the deal, signed in Moscow on Saturday, Russia and Ukraine have
agreed to divide up the former Soviet Union's assets and debts and make
separate arrangements for servicing their respective shares of the debt.
However, Mr Alexander Shokhin, Russia's deputy prime minister responsible
for the debt negotiations, said any agreement would have to be acceptable to
the ex-Soviet Union's creditors and until now they had been unhappy about
separate repayments.
